The Anti-Terrorism Police Unit (ATPU) is pursuing leads that could lead to the arrest of terrorists after a suspect in their custody revealed he has been in constant communication with Al-Shabaab fighters and their sympathisers. 

Documents obtained and seen by the nation.Africa indicate that Mr Richard Lazaro Kivatsi has been in touch with several well-known suspected terrorists based in Somalia and in Kenya. This, police allege they have discovered following a brief interview with the suspect, who is currently in their custody. 



